text: Ushimado Port was a town located in Oku District, Okayama Prefecture, Japan. As of 2003, the town had an estimated population of 7,545 and a density of 274.36 persons per km². The total area was 27.50 km². On November 1, 2004, Ushimado, along with the towns of Oku and Osafune (all from Oku District), was merged to create the city of Setouchi.
